Pulmonary mass and air meniscus sign in a 19-year-old man.
 Sacrococcygeal teratoma is rarely diagnosed in adults.
 Pulmonary mass as the presenting clinical form of the malignant variety of this germ-cell tumor is exceptional.
 We report herein such a case with the noticeable peculiarity of showing the air meniscus sign on chest roentgenographic examination.
